commits.message: Differentiate between single and batched images (#58)

pull_request.title: Differentiate between single and batched images
pull_request.body: With this PR `pystiche` can now handle single images `CxHxW` and as before batched images `BxCxHxW`. This was necessary since a `torch.utils.data.DataLoader` `torch.stack()`s images. If the image already has a batch dimension, `torch.stack()` creates erroneously a new, i.e. the fifth dimension. To prevent this `pystiche.image.read_image()` now has a `make_batched` parameter, which defaults to `True`.
